<paragraph id="BC1914043E356A48FF27F961FC8E529C" blockId="3.[151,1436,1761,2027]" pageId="3" pageNumber="46">Female (Fig. 18). Dimensions (in mm) – Total length: 15,0–16,0; Head: length: 1,6–1,8; antennal segments: I: 13,0–13,5; II: 11,8–12,0; III: 1,6–1,8; IV: 6,5–7,0; rostrum length: 1,8–1,9. Thorax: pronotum: anterior lobe length: 2,1–2,2; posterior lobe length: 1,4–1,5. Fore legs: coxa: 4,6–5,0; femur: 7,0–7,1; tibia: 2,9– 3,0; tarsus: 0,8; mid legs: femur: 13,2–13,5; tibia: 20,0–21,0; tarsus: 0,8; hind legs: femur: 17,0–17,3; tibia: 28,0–29,0; tarsus: 0,85. Abdomen length: 9,3–9,6. Last abdominal sternite with conspicuous median apical spine (Fig. 18); genital segments simple, pale to very dark.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BC1914043E356A48FF27F851FD7F52B4" blockId="3.[151,1436,1761,2027]" box="[198,697,2001,2027]" pageId="3" pageNumber="46">There is no noticeable sexual dimorphism.</paragraph>
